Plot Summary

This issue of My Greatest Adventure contains the following three stories:

  • I Was a Captive in a Space Prison!
  • I Stole Earth's Greatest Secret!
  • I Found the Tribe of Tomorrow!

It also features the following comic strips:

  • Moolah the Mystic
  • Private Pete
  • Shorty

I Was a Captive in a Space Prison

When an astronomer, Garrity, locates a new luminous body he wishes to inform others of his find. One his way to the observatory he's abducted by a group of aliens. Now held captive on a space ship he must team up with his fellow captive, Tarn, the ruler of a planet in the 5th Galaxy, to try and escape captivity.

I Stole Earth's Greatest Secret

When a strange contraption comes from the cosmos the people of Earth intemperate it as a gift from some strange alien planet; however, two scientists think otherwise. Now, Alan Case and John Farragut must use their research and wit to try and prove that danger lies within the gift from above.

I Found the Tribe of Tomorrow

After two hikers spent many days in the Andes mountains they find themselves tired and lost; however, they manage to come across a highly advanced civilization living in a primitive village. Curious at how these primitive natives created such fantastical inventions the two hikers enter the village; however, things get bad when greed sets in!

Moolah the Mystic

Moolah wins some prize money, but what's he going to do with it?

Private Pete

Pete buys a book filled with the names of many women and their phone numbers!

Shorty

Shorty visits the museum with his dog, Sport.
name: I Found the Tribe of Tomorrow

volume.name: The New Adventures of Charlie Chan

description:
The Secret of the Space Monster

Thaddeus and Rick Starr hear a report of a giant space beast nearby Jupiter’s moon Ganymede. Rick Starr suits up as Space Ranger, and leaves with Myra Mason and Cryll to investigate. While searching the space, the Ranger comes across a meteor storm. Space Ranger is unable to avoid them, but does not collide with them; instead, he discovers they are illusions. Space Ranger sends out as recon “disc”, and finds the illusions coming from an alien radar outpost on Ganymede.

Space Ranger investigates, and finds aliens inhabiting the station. Space Ranger captures one, and Cryll shape-changes into the alien. Then the two head back to the others, with Cryll pretending Space Ranger is his hostage. Using a menta-ray on the commander, they find out the aliens are rebels from the planet Korth, orbiting Procyon. They are here perfecting an illusion weapon to use to overthrow the government of Korth.

Space Ranger heads to Korth to warn the authorities there. When he arrives, though, he is captured. He rebels have an inside person in the Korth government, who arranged for Space Ranger’s capture. Cryll helps Space Ranger escape, and the rebel space fleet arrives and demands Korth surrender. Space Ranger is able to convince the leadership that the space fleet does not exist; it is all a mirage. With the invasion failed, the rebels’ inside man is arrested and Space Ranger returns home successful.

The Riddle of the Lost Race

After the theft of a rare book from the New York Space Museum, Space Ranger goes undercover. He discovers that a gang led by Ragnar-Ell is hunting for something. The Ranger’s lead brings him and secretary Myra Mason to the Valley of Ice on Saturn. They find Ragnar-Ell with a couple of space archaeologists terrorizing the natives. Space Ranger stops then, and Ragnar-Ell flees.

We find out that Ragnar-Ell and the archaeologists are after an ancient space treasure, left by a race that used to inhabit the solar system. The book stolen from the Space Museum led them to a “rosetta stone” engraved in the ice on Saturn. The next clue to the treasure is on Venus, and a race has begun. Both Ragnar-Ell’s gang and Space Ranger reach Venus, but Ragnar-Ell beats Space Ranger to the clue: a jewel.

The next piece is on Pluto, but this time Space Ranger beats Ragnar-Ell there. Space Ranger finds the “Great Sphinx of Space” and beats Ragnar-Ell to the punch. The Ranger takes the jewel from Ragnar-Ell and places the jewel in its socket, opening the sphinx. Space Ranger promises the items inside to the Solar Worlds government for the good of all mankind.

  • “Know Your Pet!”
  • “Doctor Rocket” by Henry Boltinoff
  • “Photo Ace From Outer Space”
  • “Moolah the Mystic” by Henry Boltinoff
  • “On the Planet Og” by Henry Boltinoff

Plot Summary

This issue of My Greatest Adventure contains the following three stories:

  • I Was the Robinson Crusoe of Space!
  • I Was the First Future Man!
  • We Battled the Space Giant!

It also contains the following comic strips:

  • Binky
  • Hamid the Hypnotist
  • Professor Eureka

I Was the Robinson Crusoe of Space

When Hugh, a merchant in space, and the rest of his crew fly through a meteor shower their ship ends up damaged beyond repair, crash landing on a strange planet in the nearby area. Hugh winds up being the only survivor and must harness his inner Robinson Crusoe to survive in the harsh foreign landscape and against the various predators that surround him.

I Was the First Future Man

Humanity finally has access to time travel and it's about to experiment using it's first human subject, John Franklin. When John winds up 1,000 years in the future he first finds himself amazed; however, when he realizes what an outcast he is in this strange new time his mind begins to take a turn for the worst.

We Battled the Space Giant

Three aliens have made their way to Earth and when Doctor Lane meets them they inform him of an incoming threat, Toggo, the space criminal. When Toggo arrives he begins to wreck havoc on Earth; however, there may be more to this story than the three aliens are telling.

Binky

Binky discusses the importance of staying in school.

Hamid the Hypnotist

Hamid helps a customer with pain relief.

Professor Eureka

The professor gets a new assistant who seems a tad skittish.
